<paragraph id="IAS36_18" base="SL32240" principles="no"><paranum>18</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 36"/><data name="paranum" value="18"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS36_P0156">This Standard defines <xref base="SL148458" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0106">recoverable amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0319"/></ph></xref> as the higher of an asset&#x2019;s or <xref base="SL148451" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0096">cash&#x2011;generating unit&#x2019;s<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0031"/></ph></xref> <xref base="SL148456" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0101">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> less costs of disposal and its <xref base="SL148465" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0112">value in use<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0382"/></ph></xref>.  <xref id="IAS36_X0215" base="SL195770" href="IAS36_19.dita#IAS36_19">Paragraphs 19&#x2013;57</xref> set out the requirements for measuring recoverable amount. These requirements use the term &#x2018;an asset&#x2019; but apply equally to an individual asset or a cash&#x2011;generating unit.</p></body></paragraph>